title: All Nippon Airways adds Star Wars-themed jets to its fleet
text:
All Nippon Airways adds Star Wars-themed jets to its fleet Last updated 10:46, August 19 2015 All Nippon Airways 
Japan's largest airline has added two Star Wars -themed jets to its fleet. 
All Nippon Airways, Japan's largest airline, has added two Star Wars -themed jets to its fleet. 
A Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner, painted to look like the iconic R2-D2 robot will begin a Tokyo-Vancouver route in October. The aircraft will also cover other routes later in the year. 
It will be joined by a Boeing 777-300ER inspires by a BB-8 droid that features in the seventh film: Star Wars: The Force Awakens. All Nippon Airways 
Japan's largest airline has added two Star Wars -themed jets to its fleet. 
"We look forward to providing our passengers with an engaging in-flight experience as they travel our planet," Osamu Shinobe, president of All Nippon Airways, said in the statement. 
"I'm sure (Star Wars) fans across the world will love the look," he added.
